# OrangeLion build configuration (optional).
#
# Copy this file to `theme.config` and uncomment what you need, or set the same
# names as environment variables (environment variables win). With everything
# left at its default, `./build.sh` reproduces the standard branded OrangeLion
# theme byte for byte.
#
# `theme.config` is read as plain KEY=VALUE lines; it is never executed.

# --- Variant -----------------------------------------------------------------
# branded (default) = orange palette + the lion login mark + bundled icons.
# neutral           = palette only. Drops the login mark, the product-name
#                     override, and the bundled icons, so Guacamole keeps its
#                     own logo and product name. Output defaults to
#                     dist/guacamole-theme-orangelion-neutral.jar.
# VARIANT=branded

# --- Brand palette -----------------------------------------------------------
# Set BRAND_COLOR alone to recolour the whole theme; the darker shades are
# derived from it automatically. Override the shades explicitly if you want to.
# If you pick a light brand colour, set BRAND_COLOR_DARKER to a shade that meets
# WCAG AA (>= 4.5:1) on white for link and outline-button text.
# BRAND_COLOR=#FF6200
# BRAND_COLOR_DARK=#E15700
# BRAND_COLOR_DARKER=#C24E00

# --- Login mark --------------------------------------------------------------
# Any text or emoji to show on the white login card instead of the lion emoji.
# WORDMARK=OrangeLion

# Optional logo image (SVG or PNG) shown instead of the wordmark. The path is
# relative to the repo root (or absolute). When set, the image is packed into
# the jar, exposed as a manifest resource, and the wordmark text is hidden.
# Use only artwork you have the right to use.
# LOGO=images/my-logo.svg

# --- Product name (branded builds only) --------------------------------------
# Rename the product shown on the login page and browser tab. The name is
# written into an APP.NAME translation override for each locale in LOCALES.
# APP_NAME=OrangeLion Service
# LOCALES=en nl de

# --- Output ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Output jar path (default: dist/guacamole-theme-orangelion[-neutral].jar).
# OUTPUT=dist/guacamole-theme-orangelion.jar
